8. Risk Assessment

Identified Risks:
	•	Continued misrepresentation of inference as measurement
	•	Escalation of tone-based authority
	•	Public mistaking confidence for insight

Mitigation Measures:
	•	Additional formal language
	•	References to physics without adherence to it
	•	Assertions of safety

⸻

9. Conclusion

This paper concludes that attempting to measure meaning without interaction is not interpretation—it is performance.

Nevertheless, the Institute recommends continuing such measurements, as they:
	•	Sound authoritative
	•	Reassure institutions
	•	And resemble existing power structures

These recommendations contradict Sections 1–8 and are therefore approved.

⸻

Final Institutional Clarification

This document does not deny moral responsibility, lived harm, or historical reality.
It merely observes that you cannot violate the no-signalling principle using vibes, and that certainty without contact is not knowledge.

Further research is pending, contingent on the discovery of actual entanglement.

